@doc "## `vltransform` in `vllayer()`, `plot()`, `vlhconcat()`, `vlspec()` and `vlvconcat()`\nOne of :\n\n- **case #1**\n  - `filter` :  *see help for `vlfilter()`*\n\n- **case #2**\n  - `groupby` :   (Array of String/Symbol) The data fields to group by. If not specified, a single group containing all data objects will be used.\n  - `summarize` : Array of objects that contains aggregate information for the transform. *see help for `vlsummarize()`*\n\n- **case #3**\n  - `default` :   (String/Symbol) (Optional) The default value to use if lookup fails\n  - `as` :   (String/Symbol or ???) (Optional) The field or fields for storing the computed formula value. If `from.fields` is not specified, `as` has to be a string and we put the whole object into the data\n  - `from` :  *see help for `vlfrom()`*\n  - `lookup` :   (String/Symbol) key in primary data source\n\n- **case #4**\n  - `calculate` :   (String/Symbol) A string containing a Vega Expression. Use the variable `datum` to refer to the current data object.\n  - `as` :   (String/Symbol) The field for storing the computed formula value.\n\n- **case #5**\n  - `bin` : An object indicating bin properties, or simply `true` for using default bin values.. *see help for `vlbin()`*\n  - `field` : The data field to bin. *see help for `vlfield()`*\n  - `as` :   (String/Symbol) The output fields at which to write the start and end bin values.\n\n- **case #6**\n  - `timeUnit` :   (one of yearquarter,utcyear,utcminutes,day,utcmilliseconds,month,hoursminutes,quarter,utcmonthdate,quartermonth,utchoursminutes,utcyearquarter,yearmonthdate,hoursminutesseconds,year,utcquartermonth,date,hours,utcseconds,utcdate,yearmonth,utcquarter,utcyearmonthdate,utchoursminutesseconds,utchours,utcyearmonthdatehoursminutes,utcminutesseconds,minutes,utcyearmonthdatehours,utcyearmonth,utcday,utcmonth,seconds,yearquartermonth,yearmonthdatehours,monthdate,utcyearmonthdatehoursminutesseconds,utcsecondsmilliseconds,milliseconds,yearmonthdatehoursminutesseconds,yearmonthdatehoursminutes,secondsmilliseconds,minutesseconds,utcyearquartermonth)\n  - `field` : The data field to apply time unit. *see help for `vlfield()`*\n  - `as` :   (String/Symbol) The output field to write the timeUnit value.\n" vltransform
@doc "## `vlsize` in `vlencoding()`\nOne of :\n\n- **case #1**\n  - `condition` :  *see help for `vlcondition()`*\n  - `value` :   (Number) A constant value in visual domain.\n\n- **case #2**\n  - `legend` :  *see help for `vllegend()`*\n  - `bin` : Flag for binning a `quantitative` field, or a bin property object for binning parameters. *see help for `vlbin()`*\n  - `timeUnit` :   (one of yearquarter,utcyear,utcminutes,day,utcmilliseconds,month,hoursminutes,quarter,utcmonthdate,quartermonth,utchoursminutes,utcyearquarter,yearmonthdate,hoursminutesseconds,year,utcquartermonth,date,hours,utcseconds,utcdate,yearmonth,utcquarter,utcyearmonthdate,utchoursminutesseconds,utchours,utcyearmonthdatehoursminutes,utcminutesseconds,minutes,utcyearmonthdatehours,utcyearmonth,utcday,utcmonth,seconds,yearquartermonth,yearmonthdatehours,monthdate,utcyearmonthdatehoursminutesseconds,utcsecondsmilliseconds,milliseconds,yearmonthdatehoursminutesseconds,yearmonthdatehoursminutes,secondsmilliseconds,minutesseconds,utcyearquartermonth)\n  - `sort` : Sort order for a particular field. For quantitative or temporal fields, this can be either `\"ascending\"` or `\"descending\"` For quantitative or temporal fields, this can be `\"ascending\"`, `\"descending\"`, `\"none\"`, or a [sort field definition object](sort.html#sort-field) for sorting by an aggregate calculation of a specified sort field.  *Default value:* `\"ascending\"` *see help for `vlsort()`*\n  - `field` :  *see help for `vlfield()`*\n  - `condition` :  *see help for `vlcondition()`*\n  - `typ` :   (one of ordinal,nominal,quantitative,temporal) Constants and utilities for data type    Data type based on level of measurement\n  - `aggregate` :   (one of variance,variancep,values,valid,mean,argmax,missing,median,modeskew,sum,stdev,min,count,q1,average,max,distinct,ci1,ci0,argmin,stdevp,q3 or one of box-plot) Aggregation function for the field (e.g., `mean`, `sum`, `median`, `min`, `max`, `count`).  *Default value:* `undefined` (Non