@doc "## `vlencoding` in `vllayer()`, `vlhconcat()`, `vlspec()` and `vlvconcat()`\n- `x` : X coordinates for `point`, `circle`, `square`, `line`, `rule`, `text`, and `tick` (or to width and height for `bar` and `area` marks). *see help for `vlx()`*\n- `opacity` : Opacity of the marks – either can be a value or a range. *see help for `vlopacity()`*\n- `shape` : The symbol's shape (only for `point` marks). The supported values are `\"circle\"` (default), `\"square\"`, `\"cross\"`, `\"diamond\"`, `\"triangle-up\"`, or `\"triangle-down\"`, or else a custom SVG path string. *see help for `vlshape()`*\n- `y` : Y coordinates for `point`, `circle`, `square`, `line`, `rule`, `text`, and `tick` (or to width and height for `bar` and `area` marks). *see help for `vly()`*\n- `tooltip` : The tooltip text to show upon mouse hover. *see help for `vltooltip()`*\n- `x2` : X2 coordinates for ranged `bar`, `rule`, `area`. *see help for `vlx2()`*\n- `size` : Size of the mark. - For `point`, `square` and `circle` – the symbol size, or pixel area of the mark. - For `bar` and `tick` – the bar and tick's size. - For `text` – the text's font size. - Size is currently unsupported for `line` and `area`. *see help for `vlsize()`*\n- `detail` : Additional levels of detail for grouping data in aggregate views and in line and area marks without mapping data to a specific visual channel. *see help for `vldetail()`*\n- `order` : stack order for stacked marks or order of data points in line marks. *see help for `vlorder()`*\n- `y2` : Y2 coordinates for ranged `bar`, `rule`, `area`. *see help for `vly2()`*\n- `color` : Color of the marks – either fill or stroke color based on mark type. (By default, fill color for `area`, `bar`, `tick`, `text`, `circle`, and `square` / stroke color for `line` and `point`.) *see help for `vlcolor()`*\n- `text` : Text of the `text` mark. *see help for `vltext()`*\n\n## `vlencoding` in `plot()`\n- `x` : X coordinates for `point`, `circle`, `square`, `line`, `rule`, `text`, and `tick` (or to width and height for `bar` and `area` marks). *see help for `vlx()`*\n- `row` :  *see help for `vlrow()`*\n- `opacity` : Opacity of the marks – either can be a value or a range. *see help for `vlopacity()`*\n- `column` :  *see help for `vlcolumn()`*\n- `shape` : The symbol's shape (only for `point` marks). The supported values are `\"circle\"` (default), `\"square\"`, `\"cross\"`, `\"diamond\"`, `\"triangle-up\"`, or `\"triangle-down\"`, or else a custom SVG path string. *see help for `vlshape()`*\n- `y` : Y coordinates for `point`, `circle`, `square`, `line`, `rule`, `text`, and `tick` (or to width and height for `bar` and `area` marks). *see help for `vly()`*\n- `tooltip` : The tooltip text to show upon mouse hover. *see help for `vltooltip()`*\n- `x2` : X2 coordinates for ranged `bar`, `rule`, `area`. *see help for `vlx2()`*\n- `size` : Size of the mark. - For `point`, `square` and `circle` – the symbol size, or pixel area of the mark. - For `bar` and `tick` – the bar and tick's size. - For `text` – the text's font size. - Size is currently unsupported for `line` and `area`. *see help for `vlsize()`*\n- `detail` : Additional levels of detail for grouping data in aggregate views and in line and area marks without mapping data to a specific visual channel. *see help for `vldetail()`*\n- `order` : stack order for stacked marks or order of data points in line marks. *see help for `vlorder()`*\n- `y2` : Y2 coordinates for ranged `bar`, `rule`, `area`. *see help for `vly2()`*\n- `color` : Color of the marks – either fill or stroke color based on mark type. (By default, fill color for `area`, `bar`, `tick`, `text`, `circle`, and `square` / stroke color for `line` and `point`.) *see help for `vlcolor()`*\n- `text` : Text of the `text` mark. *see help for `vltext()`*\n" vlencoding
